# Implementation Plan — Workspace Preparation for New Challenge

This plan outlines the steps to initialize the workspace for a new Kaggle challenge, following the Trinity Protocol (GEMINI.md).

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration & Orchestration
#### [MODIFY] [trinity_config.json](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/kaggle-arena/trinity_config.json)
- Set `domain` to the identified competition once confirmed.
- Prepare `thresholds` for the new mission.

#### [MODIFY] [ORCHESTRATION_RULES.json](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/kaggle-arena/.agent/rules/ORCHESTRATION_RULES.json)
- Move the target competition from `completed` (if re-entering) or add to `active`.

### Tactic Registry
#### [MODIFY] [competition_tracker.md](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/kaggle-arena/tactic_registries/competition_tracker.md)
- Add the new competition to "Aktivna Takmičenja".

### Workspace Initialization
#### [EXECUTE] `make init COMP=competition-slug`
- Download data and set up directory structure.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `make status` to verify `JudgeGuard` reflects the new active domain.
- Run `ls -R data/` to verify datasets are downloaded.

### Manual Verification
- Verify `manifest.json` is generated for the new competition (if not already present).
- Confirm with user if the selected competition is the correct target.
